<p><b>Dziga Vertov</b> (<a href="/wiki/Russian_language" title="Russian language">Russian</a>: <span lang="ru" xml:lang="ru">Дзига Вертов</span>, <a href="/wiki/Ukrainian_language" title="Ukrainian language">Ukrainian</a>: <span lang="uk" xml:lang="uk">Дзиґа Вертов</span>) <a href="/w/index.php?title=January_15_(New_Style)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="January 15 (New Style) (page does not exist)">January 15 (New Style)</a>, <a href="/wiki/1896" title="1896">1896</a>–<a href="/wiki/February_12" title="February 12">February 12</a>, <a href="/wiki/1954" title="1954">1954</a>) was a <a href="/wiki/Soviet" title="Soviet" class="mw-redirect">Soviet</a> pioneer <a href="/wiki/Documentary_film" title="Documentary film">documentary film</a> and <a href="/wiki/Newsreel" title="Newsreel">newsreel</a> director. His brothers <a href="/wiki/Boris_Kaufman" title="Boris Kaufman">Boris Kaufman</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mikhail_Kaufman" title="Mikhail Kaufman">Mikhail Kaufman</a> were also notable filmmakers.</p>
